{"questionId":"3018588","questionHtml":"<p>Use part (b) to determine the other two AS-linear functions with integer values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to find an integer value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. uses the result that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math> exactly divides <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math> OR uses a table OR uses a graph and slider OR uses systematic trial and error</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for solving&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> or solving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> or solving&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>8</mn></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>9</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)(A1)A0</strong> </em>for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3018588","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ2.2c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Use part (b) to determine the other two AS-linear functions with integer values of m, r and c.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}